body:
It was unexpected for me that this set up:

```
@Execution(CONCURRENT)
class Parent {
    @Execution(SAME_THREAD)
    class Child {
    }
}
```
results in everything running under the same thread. IMHO this should indicate that everything under `Parent` is concurrent and everything under `Child` is on the same thread. The fact that this annotation actually configures relationship with superclass is quite weird for me.
